 The material in brackets is mutilated and has been taken from <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Stanislaus Murray Hamilton, ed. &lt;i&gt;Letters to Washington and Accompanying Papers&lt;/i&gt;. 5 vols. Boston and New York, 18981902. ]">Hamilton, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Letters to Washington</span></span>, 4:13.</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0212-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0212-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0210" class="document">GW to Marshall, 9 March</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0212-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0212-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>For the negotiations between GW and Marshall for an exchange of land, see not only GWs letter of 9 Mar. to which Marshall is responding but also <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0150" class="document">Marshalls letters of 18 June 1769</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0209" class="document">8 Mar. 1770</a>.</p>

